<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880921-0143 </DOCNO><HL> Pitney Bowes Acquires Firm </HL><SO> </SO><CO> PBI </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Pitney Bowes Inc. said it acquired LPC Inc., Glen Ellyn, Ill., a privately held marketer of software for mainframe computers for a variety of mailing and direct-mail marketing functions. Terms weren't disclosed.    LPC's software helps mailers lower mail-preparation costs and postage costs. Pitney Bowes, with $2.1 billion a year in sales, is a business-equipment and financial-services company. </TEXT></DOC>